        "title": "Issue while deleting hdfs file that has space in its path, using java.lang.Process",
        "body": "<p>I have to delete file/folder from hdfs location using <code>java.lang.Process<\/code> interface.\nIt is working when path to the file/folder doesn't have spaces.\nIt returns exitcode 255 when there is space in path.<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>private static int executeProcessBuilder(String commandToExecute)  {\n    Process process = null;\n    try {\n\n        process = Runtime.getRuntime().exec(commandToExecute);\n    } catch (IOException e) {\n        LOG.error(e.getMessage());\n    }\n    try {\n        process.waitFor();\n    } catch (InterruptedException | NullPointerException  e ) {\n        LOG.error(e.getMessage());\n    }\n    return process.exitValue();\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I tried enclosing the path in double/single quotes for example<\/p>\n\n<ul>\n<li>hadoop fs -rm -skipTrash 'hdfs://pathThatHasSpace/test.csv'<\/li>\n<li>hadoop fs -rm -skipTrash \"hdfs://pathThatHasSpace/test.csv\" <\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n<p>but no luck.<\/p>\n\n<p>Can someone help in resolving this issue<\/p>\n",
